"An aircraft is in steady, unaccelerated, straight and level flight at a low subsonic speed, with no flaps extended and a coefficient of lift of 0.28. The pilot extends the flaps and slows down. The aircraft becomes steady at the new speed and remains in straight and level flight. The coefficient of lift:\n\n>>> A) Must be greater than 0.28, to maintain straight and level flight after the speed change.": "Must be greater than 0.28, to maintain straight and level flight after the speed change.",
"What is the maximum achievable load factor for an aircraft in straight and level flight at 100 kt, where the CL is 0.35 and the aircraft's CLMAX is 1.22?": "3.49",
