"While flying in the cruise with an airspeed of 280 kt, CL is 0.3. Due to expected turbulence, the speed is reduced to the turbulence penetration speed of 220 kt. The CL is now:": "0.49",
"Increasing air pressure will have the following effect on the drag of a body in an airstream (angle of attack, OAT and TAS are constant):": "the drag increases.",
"A symmetrical aerofoil set at zero angle of attack in an air stream will produce:": "drag but no lift.",
"Net Lift is generated when:": "the flow direction of a certain mass of air is changed.",
"The lift coefficient of an aerofoil section:\n\n>>> A) increases with an increase in angle of attack up to the stall.": "increases with an increase in angle of attack up to the stall.",
"Refer to figure 081-04.\nThe diagram shows the parameter Y against TAS. If horizontal flight is considered axis Y represents the:": "lift coefficient.",
"Regarding the lift formula, if density doubles, lift will:": "also double.",
"Calculate the lift coefficient from an aircraft near the stall in straight and level flight in clean configuration, given:\n \nDensity:\t1.225 kg/m3\nTAS:\t73 kt\nMass:\t7 300 kg\nWing area:\t49 m2\nG:\t9.81 m/s2": "CL = 1.69",
"Coefficient of lift is...\n\n>>> A) a variable depending upon the dynamic pressure and wing area.": "a variable depending upon the dynamic pressure and wing area.",
"Refer to figure 081-40.\nWhich of the following statements is correct?": "Line 4 corresponds to aerofoil 2.",
"Regarding a symmetrical aerofoil section, which statements are correct or incorrect?\nThe angle of attack has a negative value when the lift coefficient equals zero.\nA nose up pitching moment exists when the lift coefficient equals zero.": "1) is incorrect, 2) is incorrect.",
"During the take-off roll of a conventional aircraft, what happens to lift and drag as speed increases?": "Lift and drag both increase.",
"How does the drag coefficient change when the thickness-to-chord ratio of the wing is increased?": "It increases.",
"Considering a positively cambered aerofoil section, the pitching moment when the lift coefficient CL=0 is...": "negative.",
