"Refer to figure 081-119.\nCL vs Angle of Attack (AoA) is given with 3 positions. Each position is spaced 3° of AoA apart. How will the aircraft speed change between these positions, if the aircraft mass remains unchanged?": "Speed increases from 2 to 1 and this change is greater than the increase from 3 to 2.",
"If the wing area is increased, lift will:": "increase because it is directly proportional to wing area.",
"What is coefficient of lift, CL?": "A dimensionless number that gives the relationship between lift force per unit wing area and dynamic pressure.",
"The lift coefficient CL versus angle of attack curve of a symmetrical aerofoil section intersects the vertical axis of the graph, where the:\n\n>>> A) lift is zero.": "lift is zero.",
"A positively cambered aerofoil will generate zero lift:": "at a negative angle of attack.",
"The correct drag formula is:\n(note: RHO = density)\n\n>>> A) DRAG = CD × ½ RHO × V2 × S": "DRAG = CD × ½ RHO × V2 × S",
"A flight crew is checking the stall characteristics of an airplane close to the stall. Given the following data, what is the coefficient of lift?\n\nWing area: 13.5 m2\nDensity: 1.225 kg/m3\nSpeed: 70 kt\nMass: 1 300 kg\ng: 9.81\n\nThe coefficient of lift is:": "1.19",
"The lift coefficient of a symmetrical aerofoil section at zero angle of attack is:": "zero.",
"The coefficient of drag (CD) is…": "the ratio of drag pressure to dynamic pressure.",
"Regarding the lift formula, if airspeed doubles, lift will:\n\n>>> A) be 4 times greater.": "be 4 times greater.",
"Regarding downwash, which of the following statements is correct?\n\n>>> A) The greater the downwash, the greater the lift being generated by the aerofoil.": "The greater the downwash, the greater the lift being generated by the aerofoil.",
"An aeroplane is in steady, level flight at a constant altitude and unchanged configuration. If TAS increases slightly, what happens to the required lift coefficient, and how must the angle of attack change to maintain level flight?\n\n>>> A) CL decreases; AoA must be decreased": "CL decreases; AoA must be decreased",
"Refer to the drag formula in 2D space and assume all remaining parameters are kept constant. Drag (1) ___ with increasing altitude due to (2) ___ density.\n\n>>> A) (1) decreases; (2) decrease": "(1) decreases; (2) decrease",
"To generate a constant lift force, any adjustment in IAS must be met with an adjustment in:\n\n>>> A) Angle of attack": "Angle of attack",
"A plane is flying at 1.8 VS, what percentage of CLmax is that?": "1/(1.8)2",
"From the polar curve of the entire aircraft one can read:\n\n>>> A) the maximum CL/CD ratio and maximum lift coefficient.": "the maximum CL/CD ratio and maximum lift coefficient.",
"The lift coefficient CL versus angle of attack curve of a positively cambered aerofoil section intersects the horizontal axis of the graph:": "to the left of the origin.",
"Considering aerofoils with an angle of attack of zero, a symmetrical aerofoil has a (1) ___ CL. A positively cambered aerofoil has a (2) ___ CL. A high-speed thin aerofoil will have (3) ___ critical angle of attack, compared to the same aerofoil with higher thickness.": "(1) zero; (2) positive; (3) a reduced",
"Under what configuration is the aircraft at maximum CL/CD ratio?": "Clean configuration",
"The frontal area of a body, placed in a certain airstream is increased by a factor 3. If the shape does not alter, the form drag will increase by a factor of:": "3",
"The lift coefficient CL versus angle of attack curve of a negatively cambered aerofoil section intersects the horizontal axis of the graph:": "to the right of the origin.",
"Which of these statements about induced drag are correct or incorrect?\nA rectangular spanwise lift distribution generates more induced drag than an elliptical lift distribution.\nInduced drag increases with increasing aspect ratio.\n\n>>> A) 1) is correct, 2) is incorrect.": "1) is correct, 2) is incorrect.",
"The value of the induced drag of an aeroplane in straight and level flight at a constant weight varies linearly with:": "1 / V2",
"Wingtip vortices are ..\n\n>>> A) Stronger in clean configuration": "Stronger in clean configuration",
