"Under what conditions would we see an increase in induced drag or a high induced drag?": "With a speed reduction.",
"Induced drag may be reduced by:\n\n>>> A) an increase in aspect ratio.": "an increase in aspect ratio.",
"Which of these statements about the strength of wing tip vortices are correct or incorrect?\nAssuming no flow separation, the strength of wing tip vortices increases as the angle of attack decreases.\nThe strength of wing tip vortices decreases as the aspect ratio decreases.": "1) is incorrect, 2) is incorrect.",
"The induced drag coefficient, CDi is proportional with:\n\n>>> A) CL2": "CL2",
"With regard to planform of the wing, which is correct:": "Elliptical shaped wing has the highest lift at the root.",
"As an aeroplane slows down during the approach, the wing tip vortices and downwash will vary in intensity. How does this affect the induced angle of attack? Induced angle of attack will...": "increase, especially near the wing tip.",
"When airspeed increases, the…": "induced drag decreases.",
"The flight crew increases airspeed but they want to maintain straight and level. Therefore, the pitch attitude becomes (1) ___, the angle of attack becomes (2) ___ and the induced drag becomes (3) ___.": "(1) lower, (2) smaller, (3) smaller",
"Induced drag is caused by:": "wing tip vortices and downwash.",
"Which statement, about the effects on drag of removing external tip tanks from the wings of an aeroplane, is correct?\nParasite drag decreases.\nInduced drag decreases.": "1) is correct, 2) is incorrect.",
"Methods to reduce induced drag include...": "higher aspect ratio and adding winglets.",
"What happens if the angle of attack of a wing is increased? The pressure differential (1) ___, leading to a/an (2) ___ in the intensity of the wing tip vortices.": "(1) increases; (2) increase",
"Refer to figure 081-80.\nPolar curve (1) has a higher aspect ratio and therefore has a (2) induced drag.": "(1) A, (2) lower",
