"Which of the following best describes the airflow pattern around the aft section of an aircraft in flight?": "Around the aft section of the fuselage, the streamlines typically follow the corkscrew pattern of the wing tip vortices.",
"Which statements about induced drag are correct or incorrect?\nInduced drag increases as angle of attack increases.\nAt constant load factor, induced drag decreases with increasing aeroplane mass.": "1) is correct, 2) is incorrect.",
"Increasing the aspect ratio of a wing:": "decreases induced drag.",
