"Refer to figure 081-33.\nWhich of the four points in the attached graph depicts the maximum lift to drag ratio?": "Point 2",
"Which statements, about the effects on drag of fitting external tip tanks to the wings of an aeroplane are correct or incorrect?\nParasite drag increases.\nInduced drag increases.": "1) is correct, 2) is incorrect.",
"Refer to figure 081-120.\nIn the figure you can see the same airplane flying at two different angles of attack (AoA), 2° and 12°, and a simplified illustration of the streamlines in the 3D airflow around the wing. Assume constant speed and altitude, which angle of attack results in greater induced drag?": "12° AoA produces more induced drag than 2° AoA.",
"Which of the following aerodynamic features will decrease a wing's induced drag?\n\n>>> A) Elliptical lift distribution.": "Elliptical lift distribution.",
"An aeroplane transitions from steady straight and level flight into a horizontal co-ordinated turn with a load factor of 2, the speed remains constant and the:": "lift increases by a factor of 2",
