"What happens to the downwash angle as an aircraft extends flaps during approach preparation? It typically...": "increases.",
"Given a constant load factor, which of these statements about the variation of induced drag are correct or incorrect?\nWhen speed increases, induced drag decreases.\nWhen mass increases, induced drag increases.": "1) is correct, 2) is correct.",
"An aircraft with a low aspect ratio wing is flying at low airspeed. Which of the following statements correctly describes the behaviour of the wingtip vortices in this condition?": "Air flows spanwise around the wingtip from the high-pressure region below the wing to the low-pressure region above the wing, generating the tip vortex.",
"Wing-tip vortices are caused by…\n\n>>> A) spanwise flow of higher pressure air from beneath the wing outward and upward into the lower pressure air above the wing.": "spanwise flow of higher pressure air from beneath the wing outward and upward into the lower pressure air above the wing.",
"Which of these statements about induced drag are correct or incorrect?\nA rectangular spanwise lift distribution generates less induced drag than an elliptical lift distribution.\nInduced drag increases with increasing aspect ratio.\n\n>>> A) 1) is incorrect, 2) is incorrect.": "1) is incorrect, 2) is incorrect.",
"Which statement is correct when talking about an unswept rectangular wing?": "The flow on the upper surface of the wing has a component in wing root direction.",
"Refer to figure 081-79.\nWhich figure represents the change when the aspect ratio increases?\n\n>>> A) 3": "3",
"Which of these statements about the strength of wing tip vortices are correct or incorrect?\nAssuming no flow separation, the strength of wing tip vortices increases as the angle of attack decreases.\nThe strength of wing tip vortices decreases as the aspect ratio increases.": "1) is incorrect, 2) is correct.",
"Comparing the lift coefficient and drag coefficient for conventional aeroplanes at normal angle of attack:": "CL is much greater than CD.",
"Which of these statements about the strength of wing tip vortices are correct or incorrect?\nAssuming no flow separation, the strength of wing tip vortices decreases as the angle of attack increases.\nThe strength of wing tip vortices increases as the aspect ratio decreases.": "1) is incorrect, 2) is correct.",
"Induced drag is created by the:": "spanwise flow pattern resulting in the tip vortices.",
"The lift/drag (L/D) ratio of an airplane is...\n\n>>> A) a measure of its efficiency.": "a measure of its efficiency.",
"Which of these statements about the strength of wing tip vortices are correct or incorrect?\nAssuming no flow separation, the strength of wing tip vortices decreases as the angle of attack increases.\nThe strength of wing tip vortices is not affected by aspect ratio.\n\n>>> A) 1) is incorrect, 2) is incorrect.": "1) is incorrect, 2) is incorrect.",
"The wing planform that gives a constant lift coefficient along the whole area is...": "elliptical.",
"The fundamental difference between the aerodynamic characteristics of two and three-dimensional flow is that, in a three-dimensional flow about a wing:": "a spanwise component exists in addition to the chordwise speed component.",
"Refer to figure 081-86.\nThe same aeroplane flies at two different angles of attack (AOA), 0° and 10°. The pilot reduces the airspeed while increasing pitch from 0º to 10°, in order to maintain straight and level flight. This change will result in the following:\n\n>>> A) The lift vector's direction is changing rearwards because of a larger induced AOA.": "The lift vector's direction is changing rearwards because of a larger induced AOA.",
"Methods to reduce induced drag include:": "Increasing aspect ratio and wing twist, adding winglets",
"Excluding constants, the coefficient of induced drag (CDi) is the ratio of:\n\n>>> A) CL2 and AR (aspect ratio)": "CL2 and AR (aspect ratio)",
"Which of these statements about induced drag are correct or incorrect?\nInduced drag decreases as angle of attack increases.\nAt constant load factor, induced drag increases with increasing aeroplane mass.": "1) is incorrect, 2) is correct.",
"Decreasing the aspect ratio of a wing:\n\n>>> A) increases induced drag.": "increases induced drag.",
"Which of these statements about induced drag are correct or incorrect?\nInduced drag increases as angle of attack decreases.\nAt constant load factor, induced drag increases with decreasing aeroplane mass.": "1) is incorrect, 2) is incorrect.",
"Which of these statements about the strength of wing tip vortices are correct or incorrect?\nAssuming no flow separation, the strength of wing tip vortices increases as the angle of attack increases.\nThe strength of wing tip vortices is not affected by aspect ratio.": "1) is correct, 2) is incorrect.",
"Given a constant load factor, which of these statements about the variation of induced drag are correct or incorrect?\nWhen speed increases, induced drag increases.\nWhen mass increases, induced drag increases.": "1) is incorrect, 2) is correct.",
"What generates wake turbulence?\n\n>>> A) Wing tip vortices.": "Wing tip vortices.",
"Which of these statements about induced drag are correct or incorrect?\nAn elliptical spanwise lift distribution generates more induced drag than a rectangular lift distribution.\nInduced drag decreases with decreasing aspect ratio.": "1) is incorrect, 2) is incorrect.",
"Induced drag will be reduced if upwash ahead of the wing:": "Reduces, because induced angle of attack is decreased.",
"Two aircraft of the same type are compared, with the newer aircraft equipped with larger winglets than the older aircraft. What impact do the larger winglets have on the induced drag of the aircraft as it exits ground effect?": "The newer aircraft is less affected by the change of induced drag compared to the older aircraft, because bigger winglets reduce wingtip vortices.",
"Which of the following statements about wing planforms and spanwise lift distribution is correct?": "An elliptical wing produces more lift closer to the root.",
"Which of the following statements about the CL/CD ratio is correct?\n\n>>> A) It depends on the angle of attack.": "It depends on the angle of attack.",
"Induced drag originates from:\n\n>>> A) tip vortices.": "tip vortices.",
"Which of the following wing planforms produces the lowest induced drag? (assume zero wing twist)": "Elliptical.",
"Which one of the following statements about the lift to drag ratio in straight and level flight is correct?\n\n>>> A) At the highest value of the lift/drag ratio the total drag is lowest.": "At the highest value of the lift/drag ratio the total drag is lowest.",
"Which of these statements about induced drag are correct or incorrect?\nA rectangular spanwise lift distribution generates less induced drag than an elliptical lift distribution.\nInduced drag decreases with increasing aspect ratio.\n\n>>> A) 1) is incorrect, 2) is correct.": "1) is incorrect, 2) is correct.",
