"If the manoeuvring speed (VA) of a small single engine airplane is 102 kt and the mass is 2 550 lb, what will be the manoeuvring speed with a mass of 1 900 lb?": "88 kt",
"How does VA (EAS) change when the aeroplane's mass decreases by 19 %?": "10 % reduced.",
"After experiencing ___, the airframe structure must remain substantially intact.\n\n>>> A) the design limit load times 150%": "the design limit load times 150%",
"What is the difference between a light (CS-23) and a heavy (CS-25) aircraft when comparing their limiting load factors? The maximum limit load factor for...": "heavy aircraft will be reached at a lower value, compared to that for a light aircraft.",
"An aircraft is flown at 20% below its normal mass. Because of this, VA will be:\n\n>>> A) 10% lower.": "10% lower.",
"The relationship between the stall speed VS and VA (EAS) for a large transport aeroplane can be expressed in the following formula:": "VA >= VS × √(2.5)",
"If an aircraft is flying at a speed above VA:": "a full elevator deflection could cause a structural damage.",
"An aircraft has a mass of 60 000 kg and a limiting positive load factor of 2.5 g. VA is calculated as the EAS at which full positive elevator deflection will give the limiting load factor at the stall, and is 237 kt. If the aircraft mass is reduced to 40 000 kg by fuel burn, what will be the new VA?": "194 kt",
"Given a large transport jet aircraft with:\nMTOM: 344 t\nVS0: 140 kt\nVS1: 208 kt\n\nCalculate VA:\n\n>>> A) 328 kt": "328 kt",
"Compare the positive manoeuving limit load factors of CS-23 and CS-25 aircraft:": "CS-23 has a higher value",
"Does releasing water from a firefighting aircraft affect its limit load factor?": "No, the limit load factor does not change with aircraft weight.",
"A pilot is planning to purchase a new aerobatic aircraft and is assessing the design speeds. Using the data for the following aircraft, calculate VA.\n\nVS0: 46 kt\nVS1: 67 kt\nVFE: 75 kt\n\nLoad factor limit: 7.5": "184 kt",
"An aircraft certified under CS-23 has a design manoeuvring speed (VA) of 181 kt at a mass of 5.7 t. What is the corresponding VA at a reduced mass of 5.5 t?": "178 kt",
"The airspeed indicator shows the following values:\nGreen arc:\t70 - 165 kt\nWhite arc:\t55 - 85 kt\nVNE:\t185 kt\n\nWhat is the limit load factor of the light aircraft with a VA of 147 kt?": "4.4",
"Refer to EASA CS-23. The design manoeuvring speed, VA, is the...\n\n>>> A) maximum speed at which the aircraft can safely manoeuvre in response to gusts without exceeding its structural limits.": "maximum speed at which the aircraft can safely manoeuvre in response to gusts without exceeding its structural limits.",
"The maximum manoeuvring limit load factor for a light aeroplane (EASA CS-23) in the normal category is:\n\n>>> A) 3.8 g": "3.8 g",
"The negative manoeuvring limit load factor for a light aeroplane in the utility category in the clean configuration may not be more than:": "-1.76 g",
"The stall speed line in the manoeuvring load diagram runs through a point where the:\n\n>>> A) speed = VS, load factor = +1.": "speed = VS, load factor = +1.",
"By what percentage does VA (EAS) change when the aeroplane's mass decreases by 10 %?": "5 % lower.",
"What do the horizontal and vertical lines denote in the manoeuvring envelope (V-N) diagram?": "EAS and load factor.",
"What is the maximum positive maneuvering limit load factor for a light airplane in the utility category when in a clean configuration?": "4.4 g",
"Calculate the VA for an aerobatic aeroplane with a VS0 of 43 kt and a VS1 of 58 kt.": "142 kt",
"Which of the following statements about changes in the aircraft mass and its design manoeuvring speed, VA, is correct?": "A decrease in aircraft mass results in a decrease in VA.",
"For an aeroplane with one fixed value of VA the following applies. VA is:": "the speed at which the aeroplane stalls at the manoeuvring limit load factor at MTOW.",
"Given:\n \nVS:\t45 kt\nVA:\t100 kt\nVNO:\t125 kt\nVNE:\t160 kt\n\nWhich of the following speed ranges should be used for exercising stalls?\n\n>>> A) 45 kt to 100 kt": "45 kt to 100 kt",
"The stall speed line in the manoeuvring load diagram of a large transport airplane runs through a point where the:": "speed = VA, load factor = limit load factor.",
"Calculate the new VA speed for an aircraft that initially has a VA speed of 181 kts at 5.7 tonnes, but now has a mass of 4.5 tonnes...\n\n>>> A) 161 kt": "161 kt",
