"Refer to figure 081-92.\nWhich of the curves provides the greatest load factor for a given gust?\n\n>>> A) 1": "1",
"Which of the following is a correct design gust value factor applied in certification under EASA CS-25?": "66 ft/sec at VB.",
"An aeroplane in straight and level flight at 300 kt is subjected to a sudden disturbance in speed. Assuming the angle of attack remains constant initially and the load factor reaches a value of approximately 1.2:": "the speed will have increased by 30 kt.",
