"For a fixed-pitch propeller, the blade angle of attack:\n\n>>> A) decreases during the take-off.": "decreases during the take-off.",
"Propeller pitch varies from hub to tip...": "to maintain a constant angle of attack along the length of the blade.",
"What occurs to a constant speed propeller's blade angle and RPM when an aeroplane wing's angle of attack is reduced during level flight?\n\n>>> A) The blade angle increases and the RPM remains constant.": "The blade angle increases and the RPM remains constant.",
"Which of the following statements about a constant-speed propeller true?": "It maintains high efficiency across a range of speeds.",
"Refer to figure 081-35.\nSelect the correct terms with regards to the given lines:": "(1) thrust, (3) torque",
"What happens to the blade pitch of a constant pitch propeller on ground roll during takeoff?": "Remains constant",
"Refer to figure 081-16.\nA rotating propeller blade element produces an aerodynamic force F that may be resolved into two components:\n\n• a force T perpendicular to the plane of rotation (thrust)\n• a force R generating a torque absorbed by engine power\n\nThe diagram representing a rotating propeller blade element during the cruise is:\n\n>>> A) diagram 1.": "diagram 1.",
"What is the ratio between engine torque and propeller torque on constant RPM?": "Equal to 1.",
"A small multi-engine piston airplane encounters an anti-icing failure on one propeller while crossing the Alps at FL220. Due to the weather conditions, ice builds up on the propeller with the failed anti-icing system. Which of the following statements describes a possible hazard of such icing problem?": "Reduced propeller efficiency means that the aircraft can NOT maintain cruising altitude.",
"Refer to figure 081-16.\nWhich diagram shows the propeller being driven solely by engine torque?": "1 and 2.",
"Why is a propeller blade twisted from root to tip?": "To maintain a constant angle of attack along the whole length of the propeller blade.",
"Your airplane is equipped with a fixed-pitch propeller. During the take-off run, the blade angle of attack will (1) ___ and the propeller thrust will (2) ___.": "(1) decrease; (2) decrease",
"Refer to figure 081-20.\nThe correct sequence of cross-sections representing propeller blade twist is:": "sequence 1.",
