"Refer to figure 081-35.\nThe thrust force vector is shown by arrow number...": "1",
"Assuming that the RPM remains constant throughout, the angle of attack of a fixed pitch propeller will:": "decrease with increasing airspeed.",
"What happens to propeller efficiency and power absorption if the chord of its propeller blades increases?": "Propeller efficiency decreases and power absorption increases.",
"Refer to an airplane with a fixed-pitch propeller during the ground roll for take-off. The blade-pitch of the propeller will…": "remain constant.",
"Refer to figure 081-109.\nWhat is shown in the attached figure?\n\n>>> A) A: Slip\nB: Effective pitch\nC: Geometric pitch": "A: Slip",
"For an aircraft with a two position variable pitch propeller, what should the propeller pitch be?": "Fine during climb and coarse during cruise.",
"Refer to figure 081-31.\nThe designators D, C, and B (in this order) correspond to...": "helix angle, blade angle, and angle of attack.",
"Refer to an airplane with a constant-speed propeller during a glide with idle power and maintaining a constant airspeed. When the pilot is pushing the propeller lever forward, it will…": "decrease the pitch angle and increase RPM.",
