"Which of the following propellers is most efficient over a wide range of flight speeds?": "Variable-pitch propeller",
"Refer to the take-off ground roll with an airplane equipped with a constant speed propeller. The blade pitch will…": "increase.",
"What happens to the blade angle of an airplane with a variable pitch propeller during the take-off ground roll?": "It increases.",
"Which statement about a propeller is correct or wrong?\nA propeller with little blade twist is referred to as being in fine pitch.\nA propeller with significant blade twist is referred to as being in coarse pitch.\n\n>>> A) 1) is incorrect, 2) is incorrect.": "1) is incorrect, 2) is incorrect.",
"Which statement are correct or incorrect when comparing a fixed pitch propeller with a constant speed propeller?\nA constant speed propeller reduces fuel consumption over a range of cruise speeds.\nA constant speed propeller improves take-off performance as compared with a coarse fixed pitch propeller.": "1) is correct, 2) is correct.",
"When flying an aircraft with a fixed pitch propeller at constant power and decreasing true airspeed, what effect does this have on the blade angle of attack and thrust produced?": "Increases; Increases",
"Refer to figure 081-26.\nThe variation of propeller efficiency of a fixed pitch propeller with TAS at a given RPM is shown in:": "figure 4.",
"Which of the following statements about propeller parameters is correct?\n\n>>> A) Propeller angle of attack is the angle between the blade chord line and the relative airflow.": "Propeller angle of attack is the angle between the blade chord line and the relative airflow.",
