"What condition would lead to a worse angle of attack on the fin, if one engine of a multi-engine airplane fails?\n\n>>> A) Increased angle of attack on the inoperative engine's side.": "Increased angle of attack on the inoperative engine's side.",
"What conditions are used to determine VMCL?": "Landing configuration; Full power thrust setting on the operating engine(s)",
"A commercial transport aircraft encounters a pressurisation issue and needs to be flown back to the maintenance facility without any passengers or cargo. What should the crew be aware of regarding the one-engine inoperative controllability after take-off?": "A decreased safety margin to VMC due to the low operating speeds associated with low mass",
"Which of these statements about VMCG determination are correct or incorrect?\nVMCG may be determined using both lateral and directional control.\nDuring VMCG determination, the lateral deviation from the runway centreline may be not more than 30 ft.\n\n>>> A) 1) is incorrect, 2) is correct.": "1) is incorrect, 2) is correct.",
"Refer to an engine failure of a twin-engine airplane with clockwise rotating propellers after take-off. Assume the pilot flying maintains a bank angle of 0° and does not change the power setting, which situation would lead to the largest rudder deflection?": "Left crosswind, left engine failure.",
"Which statement about minimum control speed is correct?": "VMCA depends on the airport density altitude, and the location of the engine on the aeroplane (aft fuselage or wing).",
